Happy Caturday from Delilah! She is a beautiful Tortie with a lovely sweet face and she can usually be found on a high shelf or chair, lounging or sleeping but always observing. Delilah is very sweet but like many adult cats she does need time to warm up. She enjoys a quieter home with a slower pace to have the opportunity to get to know you fully and really come into her own. Once she does she is in love. Delilah likes having your attention and is great with other cats but prefers a home without dogs. She loves when you pet her, play with her, and feed her! Delilah is about one to two years old. Contact Goodmewsrescue@gmail.com to meet her.

Isabel is a snuggly lil' pocket pittie who charms everyone she meets with her irresistible smile! This affectionate girl is just 45 lbs., and has an undeniable joie de vivre about her, and she doesn't let the fact that she has some arthritis in her legs stop her from chasing the ball and telling people she wants to play! Isabel is truly a lover of a pup who is friendly with everyone she encounters!
Despite Isabelâ€™s HAPPY & loving personality, she came into the shelter in very sad shape in early August. She was overbred, abandoned, and had a skin infection over most of her body. With TLC, she is recovering very well and ready to find a family who will cherish her!! This nugget of sunshine belongs in a home! Please help us to spread the word about this sweet girl - you could be the hero Isabel needs!

Bubble (formally Plum) has been with us now for 8 months, is doing really well and its hard to imagine our lives without her. Originally she had some anxiety complex due to living in a cage before HKDR. Today this has almost gone and loves nothing more than being outside in the park, chasing a ball and interacting with other dogs (most of the time). Our complex has a number of other dog owners and this has not only given us support but also introduced us to a lot of new people. Bubble loved the â€œPeak to Fongâ€ and she is so popular with our friends and colleagues that she fund raised enough donations to come in at No. 13!
We have received great support from Cactus in the early months when we had questions and we really appreciate this. This motivated me to arrange for our company â€œVFâ€ and â€œLee Jeansâ€ to bring a large amount of volunteers over to â€œTai Po Homing Centreâ€ in November to help out as part of our team building, we will do this again in the New Year.
